The possible mechanism of insertion of phosphorous supported functional groups on the surface of GQD is demonstrated in Fig. S9. After the structural confirmation of FR-GQD solution, it is used as a transparent liquid for the further experiment of the flame retardant test. For the preparation of the flame retardant sample, as prepared FR-GQD transparent solution in water was used to coat a few pieces of cloths of different colours (Green, red and cyan) (Scheme 1
                     ) [size:3.5*5]. These cloth pieces were allowed to dry under vacuum oven at 60 °C overnight, while control cloth samples of respective colours remain uncoated. Both the samples were tested at the same time in the air with ethanol flame [Fig. 4
                     ]. The FR-GQD coated cloth emitted little smoke initially without catching fire even after continuous heating up to >300s (5 min ). It has maintained almost in its initial form with just colour converted to black colour and little tilting was observed. On heating phosphorous functional groups up to 300 °C it has turned into black colour due to the formation of polymeric structure, which protected fibres beneath [28,29]. On the other hand, the control sample was observed to catch fire within 5s and completely burnt within 15s to convert into small thin mass. Flame test of GQD coated sample, as well as PPA/NaH2PO4 sample, were also carried out. In case of GQD coated cloth, it got burnt out in 17s and hence it was not acted as the flame retardant. In case of PPA/NaH2PO4 coated cloth sample, little resistance is observed in flame test but it also got burnt out within 35s. The possible mechanism of conversion of GQD to FR-GQD is shown in (Fig. S10). Possibly intramolecular and the intermolecular reaction had taken place during the flame test, which helps to form an active char to limit ingress of oxygen on the surface of the cotton cloth fabric by the thermal condensation of phosphorous functional groups present on GQD [10,17] (Fig. S11). The loading of FR-GQD with respect to the mass of blank cotton cloth was approximately 5.78% for 3 times coatings to provide efficient flame retardant property (Table S3). Also, the loading data of GQD, PPA/NaH2PO4 with observation after the flame test is given (Tables S1 to S2). Different colour cloths had also coated with FR-GQD solution (Fig. S12).
